rComments: Seriously one of the best profs at uOttawa. I've had many classes with him, he really does care about us doing well and puts a lot of effort into his teaching. His TAs always give great feedback.
Good teaching & fair marking. Highly recommended.
Love this guy! The class is a lot of work but Robert is a gem!
took his 4 main classes, always a good time
Great professor for CSI2510 and CSI2520. He explains everything really clearly. Lots of small assignments which make for good practice. Keep up with the assignments and the class should go well.

This professor is one of the best one I've had. There may be a fair amount of assignments, but they make you learn. The professor is sweet and always present to answer questions. I've also had him for CSI 2772 and CSI 2510, I would take any other course with him again!
I would avoid at all cost. Professor puts little to no effort in making the exams understandable. He takes forever to answer his emails and the assignments are never ending!

Robert Laganière really cares for his students, and knows and conveys the material very well. This is meant as a fair warning if you are taking one of his classes: attend the lectures!! The lectures are very important with Laganière and can literally be a matter of passing or failing. However, if you attend class, you'll easily pass it!

This is my third time being taught by Laganiere. He is an outstanding teacher and makes challenging concepts clear. Assignments were very straightfoward if you attend class. We had a final project and an exam split into a theoretical and practical (coding) part, all of which were also reasonably easy.

One of the best profs ever! His explanations are always clear, engaging and leave no room for confusion. Always prepared for his lectures and always has a visual aid to help students better understand data structures and algorithms!

un des meilleur profs et cours que j'ai eu a uOttawa. il veut vraiment la réussite de se ses élèves et donne toujours la possibilité d'améliorer note note et de rendre le cours plus interessant pour nous. meilleur cours CSI 4e année

Laganiere's an all-around great prof. He's very knowledgeable in the programming languages he teaches and conveys them well. You can easily get help or resources online for the labs or homework. There are lots of homework assignments, but none of them are ridiculously hard.

It's a pretty boring class overall, but the expectations are always very clear. Assignments can be challenging and take time. The exams are totally fair and you can easily study with the past materials for them. I found that the tutorials weren't very clear or helpful, though.
He gives a lot of assignments and quizzes. But still the best teacher ever. Exams are never a surprise. Would have again

The best teacher in CSI imo. I specifically switched from English class to this one just to have this teacher. I have him again in CSI2520 and I do not regret. tests are exactly what you'd expect, final as well. Assignments are kinda hard but that's how you learn.

Great prof. He explains algorithms in a simple way so we can understand them and uses props and clever analogies to teach them. He always seems to be in a good mood and ready to answer students' questions. Programming assignments (2) are tricky but exams are fair.
Really good teacher, knows what he's talking about.
Just amazing

I strongly recommend taking this prof. His lectures are clear, and when he sees that the class doesn't get a concept, he starts over and goes through it more slowly. He's approachable and kind.  If you have the choice between this prof and Moura for CSI2110, then trust me, you should take Laganiere even if your French is mediocre.
Had him for 2 classes, and he was great for both. What can I say, he's just a good guy and a good prof. Exams are just like what you did in class also if that worries you
Tres bon prof, explique tres bien la matiere et tres drole desfois. Recommande fortement.

Very nice and respectful. One of the best profs so far. Makes jokes from time to time. Teaches very well and grades fairly. Had him for three classes : CSI2510, SEG2505 and CSI2772. The class is easy if you do the homework, lab sessions for CSI2510 are not useful.

This course was a disaster. He can't explain in class, for 3 classes we stalled on one thing as every time he attempted to explain it, he confuses himself and us even more. Despite of his lacking, he is a hard marker, gives difficult assignments, confusing wordings of his assignments, with lots of mistakes. You got to teach yourself in this class.
Great teacher, had for CSI 2772, SEG 2505, CSI 2510
Second class I take with him, he is clear and he shows interest and passion towards the subject being taught. You will definitely learn a lot with him

He never actually tries. Promised a final project, similar to 2105 however he doesn't care. GitHub & Google Docs usage was horrid. Another student over wrote your work? No care. Disrespects course outline OR grading criteria. Doesn't know the platform used (Android), gives broken code! Its an easy course, tsk its SEG, open book. AVOID, take Tim

He was really good had good powerpoints and gave good examples in class. Exams are really easy if you put minimum effort listening in class. His examples in class are very similar to the ones in the exam
simplement le meilleur
Vraiment juste.
Vraiment très gentil, terre à terre, juste.
Vraiment gentil, toujours prêt à aider, pas trop difficile sur les notes, très juste.
